  "title": "Operation Executive (Middle Distillate) – Oil & Gas Trading",
  "description": "<p><strong>Description</strong><br />This is an integrated trading organization with a strong oil and gas asset base. Due to internal mobility, an exciting opportunity has arisen for an Operator to join a high-performing trading desk.<br /><br /><strong>Role</strong><br />Reporting to the Operations Manager, the Operations Executive is responsible for supporting trading desk operations by ensuring timely and accurate communication of cargo nominations to terminals, shipowners, and counterparties. The role focuses on minimizing operational delays and ensuring full alignment with contractual obligations. It requires close coordination with storage terminals and vessel operators to monitor loading and discharge activities and to resolve operational issues in real time. A solid understanding of trade finance, including Letters of Credit (LCs), invoicing, and demurrage management, is essential. The position also involves maintaining accurate and up-to-date operational records within internal systems to support effective reporting, audit readiness, and regulatory compliance.<br /><br /><strong>Requirements</strong><br />The successful candidate will ideally hold a degree in Maritime Studies or a related discipline, with a minimum of three years’ experience in oil cargo operations, preferably within an international trading company or major. The ideal profile is meticulous, proactive, and entrepreneurial, with a strong ability to independently troubleshoot and resolve operational issues. Excellent communication skills are essential for managing stakeholder relationships and ensuring smooth, efficient operations.<br /><br /><strong>Apply</strong><br />To apply, please submit your resume to James Yan at <a href=\"mailto:James@kerryconsulting.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">James@kerryconsulting.com</a>, quoting the job title and reference number JA35257. Only successful shortlisted candidates will be notified.<br /><br />Licence No: 16S8060<br />Registration no: R22104741</p>",
